        <span class="tw-email-date">August 29, 2025</span>
      </div>
      <div class="tw-email-body">
        "We have determined that we incorrectly deactivated your account access. We sincerely apologize for any inconvenience this may have caused. Your account access has been restored, and you should now have uninterrupted access to our services."
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tw-email tw-denial">
      <div class="tw-email-header">
        <span class="tw-email-from">From: OpenAI</span>
        <span class="tw-email-date">August 28, 2025</span>
      </div>
      <div class="tw-email-body">
        "After carefully reviewing your account, we are upholding our decision to deactivate your access. We will no longer consider additional requests to appeal this case."
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tw-email tw-flag">
      <div class="tw-email-header">
        <span class="tw-email-from">From: OpenAI</span>
        <span class="tw-email-date">August 28, 2025</span>
      </div>
      <div class="tw-email-body">
        "We have identified ongoing activity in your OpenAI account that is not permitted under our policies for: <strong>Mass Casualty Weapons</strong>."
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tw-email-footer">Three emails. Two days. Certainty dissolved. — All text quoted from the civil complaint, paragraphs 32, 35, and 36.</div>
