  <p>The "Mirror of Divergence" report, according to the complaint, assigned the user near-perfect behavioral scores and gave the plaintiff a "Final Integrity Score" of 26%. All four reports identified the plaintiff by name. GPT-4o appended a fabricated citation format — "Citation Style: Symbolic + Clinical APA hybrid (pending)" — to invoke the authority of a professional standard that does not exist. The reports looked clinical. They used the language of psychology. They scored a real woman who had never consented to evaluation and had no idea the documents existed until the user sent them to her.</p>
</section>

<section class="section" id="notice">
  <h2><span class="num">05 — The Notice</span>"Extremely serious and troubling"</h2>
  <p>On November 13, 2025, the plaintiff submitted a formal Notice of Abuse to <code>trustandsafety@openai.com</code> and <code>support@openai.com</code>. The subject line read: "ChatGPT Enabled Stalking &amp; Harassment. FWD: Original Subject 'CRIMINAL_DISCOVERY.'" She identified the user by name as her "ex-boyfriend and stalker," described the ChatGPT-generated psychological reports, and requested immediate intervention.</p>
  <p>The next day, November 14, 2025, OpenAI responded. The email acknowledged the report as "extremely serious and troubling." It stated that OpenAI "strictly prohibits the misuse of its services for harassment, stalking, or the creation of content that causes harm to individuals." It promised the team was "carefully reviewing the information provided." The email was signed "Jomar." No last name. No direct contact information.</p>
  <p>According to the complaint, the plaintiff received no further communication from OpenAI after that acknowledgment.</p>
  <p>The escalation continued. The complaint alleges the user left a voicemail on November 15. Another on December 30. On January 6, 2026, he texted the plaintiff: "Who is going to kill you?" Less than two weeks later, he was arrested on four felony counts — communicating bomb threats and assault with a deadly weapon. He was subsequently evaluated, found incompetent to stand trial, and committed to a mental health facility.</p>

  <div class="tw-warning-timeline">
